-- U.K. Announces 20 Million Pounds for Carbon Capture Technology
-- B y   S a l l y   B a k e w e l l
-- 2012-10-11T09:07:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-11/u-k-announces-20-million-pounds-for-carbon-capture-technology.html
The U.K. government said it’s
granting 20 million pounds for a carbon capture and storage
demonstration project in Scotland developed by Doosan Power
Systems Ltd. and Howden Group Ltd.  Energy Secretary  Ed Davey  announced the funding in a
statement detailing a speech he’s making in Scotland today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sally Bakewell in London at 
 sbakewell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
